---
import SectionLabel from "../../../elements/SectionLabel.astro";
import Heading from "../../../elements/Heading.astro";
import BodyText from "../../../elements/BodyText.astro";
---

<section
  class="bg-rh-warm-light dark:bg-rh-warm-dark min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center py-32 md:py-48 px-6 md:px-10"
  id="agitation-section"
>
  <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[1400px]">
    <!-- Centered Billboard: Terminal Header + Headline -->
    <div
      class="flex flex-col items-center text-center w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto mb-16 md:mb-24"
    >
      <SectionLabel text="> SYS.DIAGNOSTIC // THE_TWO_TRAPS" centered />
      <Heading class="agitation-reveal mt-6">
        Expertise is invisible.<br />
        Audiences are rented.<br />
        <span class="text-rh-ember">Trust is broken.</span>
      </Heading>
    </div>

    <!-- Two-column layout: Copy left, Counter right -->
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-24 items-center w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto"
    >
      <!-- Left: Copy -->
      <div class="agitation-reveal">
        <BodyText class="mb-6">
          Right now, you are trapped in one of two realities. Either you have a
          decade of world-class expertise but refuse to play the performative
          marketing game, leaving you invisible. Or, you've built a massive
          audience, but your back-end is an awkward 8th-grade dance, <strong
            class="font-bold text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk"
            >people show up to see you, but leave because they don't connect
            with each other.</strong
          >
        </BodyText>
        <BodyText>
          In an era where AI can manufacture infinite noise, authority is faked
          and trust is broken. When anyone can generate 'expertise' with a
          prompt, you can no longer compete on content alone. The only way to
          survive is to build a culture that cannot be automated. <strong
            class="font-bold text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk"
            >Community is your true moat.</strong
          > And both of these traps, being invisible or bleeding an audience, <strong
            class="font-bold text-rh-ember"
            >are solved by the exact same architecture.</strong
          >
        </BodyText>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Decay Counter -->
      <div
        class="agitation-reveal border border-rh-ink/10 dark:border-rh-chalk/10 p-10 md:p-14"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
          <span class="block w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-rh-ember/40"></span>
          <span
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ink/40 dark:text-rh-chalk/40"
            >LIVE DIAGNOSTIC</span
          >
        </div>

        <!-- Big Counter -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <p
            class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ink/40 dark:text-rh-chalk/40 mb-3"
          >
            BROADCASTS_SENT_TODAY:
          </p>
          <p
            class="font-mono text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-rh-ink dark:text-rh-chalk tabular-nums tracking-tight"
            id="decay-counter"
          >
            0
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contrast Stats -->
        <div
          class="border-t border-rh-ink/10 dark:border-rh-chalk/10 pt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-6"
        >
          <div>
            <p
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ink/40 dark:text-rh-chalk/40 mb-2"
            >
              REAL_CONNECTIONS:
            </p>
            <p
              class="font-mono text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-rh-ember tabular-nums"
            >
              12
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p
              class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ink/40 dark:text-rh-chalk/40 mb-2"
            >
              RETENTION_RATE:
            </p>
            <p
              class="font-mono text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-rh-ink/15 dark:text-rh-chalk/15 tabular-nums"
            >
              0.02%
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  import { gsap } from "gsap";
  import { ScrollTrigger } from "gsap/ScrollTrigger";
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

  // Reveal animations
  gsap.fromTo(
    ".agitation-reveal",
    { opacity: 0, y: 50 },
    {
      opacity: 1,
      y: 0,
      duration: 1,
      stagger: 0.3,
      ease: "power3.out",
      scrollTrigger: {
        trigger: "#agitation-section",
        start: "top 70%",
      },
    },
  );

  // Decay counter - starts when visible, rapidly increments
  const counterEl = document.getElementById("decay-counter");
  if (counterEl) {
    let count = 3_847_291_044;
    let running = false;

    function formatNumber(n: number): string {
      return n.toLocaleString("en-US");
    }

    function tick() {
      if (!running) return;
      count += Math.floor(Math.random() * 800) + 200;
      counterEl!.textContent = formatNumber(count);
      requestAnimationFrame(tick);
    }

    ScrollTrigger.create({
      trigger: "#agitation-section",
      start: "top 60%",
      onEnter: () => {
        if (!running) {
          running = true;
          counterEl.textContent = formatNumber(count);
          tick();
        }
      },
    });
  }
</script>
